<p>In <a href="http://www.dabeaz.com/modulepackage/ModulePackage.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Modules and Packages: Live and Let Die!"</a>, page 28 (see also <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0oTh1CXRaQ0" rel="nofollow">the video</a>), it's said that: </p>  <blockquote>   <p>You can force-reload a module, but you're    never supposed to do it.</p> </blockquote>  <p>Can anyone explain why we are not supposed to reload modules in Python?</p>